A site for sore eyes.  
Welcome, visitor. I'm one of the co-hosts on the Wanderers in the 4th Dimension podcast, a weekly show dedicated to Doctor Who, both classic & modern, plus anything in-between. This is my personal blog, but since so much of my free-time is devoted to the podcast, this blog is inherently a reflection of that devotion, though occasionally other musings find there way here as well. I'm someone who likes to muck about with Photoshop, so much (though, by no means all) of the content you'll find here is of my own creation.

body:
Finally watched Bad Samaritan

After waiting for like ten years for it to come out in Europe …

David is awesome as usual, scary cold bastard. He plays psychos way too well. And so is Robert Sheehan, he is very good and plays a very conflicted character very well

But, can someone rewrite this movie with a better backstory for Cale, less implausible circumstances and a better ending?

I feel a bit cheated like we could have had a PERFECT bite your nails edge of the seat thriller. The basics were there and all in all it still made me jump and get my heart hammering. BUT man the ending and some circumstances were like dude really?

I liked it a lot and I didn’t. So yeah…
